name Beduine im Hemd
serves 4
desc Spiced minced beef roll in puff pastry.
note Serve with a salad.
tags main, meat, mena

# Preparation

- 600 g minced beef
Sear over high heat.

- 2 onions
- chilli
- "fresh ginger"
Dice the onions, finely dice the chilli and grate the ginger. Add everything to the beef
and cook together.
-> mince

- 50 g pine nuts
@nodep
Toast in a dry pan until golden.
-> pine nuts

- 40 g raisins
- 3 tbsp sour cream
- 1 tsp cinnamon
- garlic
- "ground cumin"
- "fresh coriander"
- salt
- pepper
- Tabasco
- "sweet chili sauce"
- "mango chutney"
@ pine nuts
@ mince
Press the garlic. Add the pine nuts, raisins, sour cream and spices to the beef, season
well and leave to cool.

- 2 packs puff pastry
- 1 egg
Roll out the puff pastry. Spread the beef mixture over the pastry sheets and roll up.
Seal the edges with egg white. Place seam-side down on a baking sheet and brush with
egg yolk. Bake at 180°C for 30-40 minutes.
